data.enText: done in order to prepare for sth

data.chText: 为迎接总统来访，当局已预先进行了安全检查。
data.enText: Security checks had been carried out preparatory to (= to prepare for) the President's visit.

value.def: Preparatory actions are done before doing something else as a form of preparation or as an introduction.

example.ex: At least a year's preparatory work will be necessary before building can start.
example.tran: 在开始动工之前至少要做一年的准备工作。

example.ex: ...preparatory talks for this week's summit in the Maldive Islands.
example.tran: 为本周在马尔代夫群岛召开的峰会举行的预备会谈

value.def: If one action is done preparatory to another, it is done before the other action, usually as preparation for it.

example.ex: Sloan cleared his throat preparatory to speaking...
example.tran: 斯隆清了清嗓子，准备讲话。

example.ex: She lit the oven, preparatory to putting the pie into it.
example.tran: 她把烤箱加热，准备把馅饼放进去。

trans: 预备学校(英国为准备升入公学者而设的私立小学)
